  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Social Inclusion for Peacebuilding in the ethnic territories of Choc&#xF3;</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will benefit social and ethnic territorial organisations in the department of Choc&#xF3;, specifically in the jurisdiction served by the Social Pastoral of the Diocese of Quibd&#xF3; and the AfroColombian community councils represented by the organisation Cocomopoca, located in the municipalities of Atrato, Llor&#xF3;, Bagad&#xF3;, Certegui, Carmen de Atrato, Bojay&#xE1;, R&#xED;o Quito, and Quibd&#xF3;. 
Its main objective is that the pastoral agents of the Diocese of Quibd&#xF3; and the leaders of COCOMOPOCA participate, lead and promote peace actions in the framework of the implementation of the peace accords and facilitate tools of good governance for their actions in the region.
The implementation of training processes for leaders and young people, updating and construction of tools of governance of COCOMOPOCA&apos;s ethnic authority and institutional policies of Pastoral Social, political actions of lobby and advocacy, legal accompaniment and litigation, monitoring and verification of what is happening in the territories (ethnic territorial focused development plans (PEDETs), Atrato River Ruling T622, advocacy actions, humanitarian missions, etc.) are planned.</narrative>
  </description>
